response.Q0: I clicked on the end nodes to see the value and then go to that value. I did not account for internode losses and switched strategies when I saw the pattern
response.Q1: The strategy I ended up using was, clicking the first 3 to check which is the lowest or green. Then go down that row to node 4 to inspect the red or green. If green I inspect the surrounding nodes. If both nodes 4 are green, I take the highest value to counter uninspected node losses.
response.Q2: Not that difficult. Once you realize that there are specific nodes you can choose to help, it gets easier.
